  "texts": [
    "We utilized the gender_id column to identify sex, as the standard documentation intend for this column to represent biological sex (https://ohdsi.org/web/wiki/doku.php?id=document ation:vocabulary:gender/).",
    "Note that only two options exist (female concept_id = 8532 and male concept_id = 8507), and that accurate sex and gender information may be limited depending on the institution or EHR collection of sex information.",
    "Analysis of time to AD diagnosis includes utilization of Kaplan-Meier survival curves fitted with 95% CIs and two-sided log-rank test to compare survival curves between groups.",
    "Sex-stratified curves were also fitted.",
    "Cox proportional hazard models were utilized to obtain unadjusted HRs and aHRs by demographics and/or visit information, with and without stratification by recruitment age or birth year, and with 95% CIs."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}